<!--
Perceive-act loop, v3. The same shared always-socket agent (`agent.bsx`) as v1/v2, but
with NO in-process clients: instead a second server, an `HttpServer`, serves a wasm
browser head. A browser tab loading the head page boots the wasm `beet` binary, which
connects back to the agent's socket server as the `head` client and serves `take-photo`
(the real webcam), `speak-text` (the Web Speech API) and `set-emotion` (a rendered `<img>`
face). A device body (eg the esp Alvik) can connect for `apply-heading`; none runs here.

Two servers in one process, each its own root with its own `BootOnLoad`, both bound to
all interfaces so a phone on the LAN can load the head page and connect back: the agent's
`SocketServer` (all interfaces by default) on `:8338`, and the head `HttpServer` (all
interfaces via its `host` field) on `:8337`. Install the wasm binary once (the same
single binary every wasm example mounts, at `assets/wasm/beet.wasm`), then run both
servers (the socket and http servers both default-boot, so no --server flag is needed):

    beet build-wasm --release --package=beet-cli --bin=beet --features=web_examples,web_head --out=assets/wasm/beet.wasm
    beet --main=examples/perceive_act/main-v3.bsx
    # for running on esp32, cd ../beet_esp and load
    beet load templates/alvik/perceive-act-body.bsx

Then open https://<this-host>:8337 (any device on the LAN, one-time certificate warning)
or plain http://127.0.0.1:8337 locally, and grant camera access; the head derives the
agent's socket url (and its ws/wss scheme) from the page location. The webcam needs a
secure context, so both servers declare `Tls`, serving https/wss from a cached
self-signed cert while loopback http and native ws stay served, see the README.
Needs `OPENAI_API_KEY`. `sockets` links the websocket transport, `thread` the agent
LLM, `secure` the TLS serving; the page + assets ride the default native router.
-->
<Fragment>
	<!-- the head routes, wasm binary and eye sprites live workspace-relative -->
	<StoreRoot src="../.."/>
	<CrateCheck features="thread,sockets,secure"/>
	<!-- the always-socket agent: a socket server whose head capabilities forward to the
	     browser head over the socket, bound by the `whoami` handshake. -->
	<Template src="examples/perceive_act/agent.bsx"/>
	<!-- the head server: serves the head page + the wasm binary + the examples/assets the
	     browser fetches. Its own root, so its route tree is isolated from the agent.
	     `Tls` serves it https (loopback http stays served), the secure context a LAN
	     device's webcam needs; the agent socket declares the same. -->
	<Router {(HttpServer{host:[0,0,0,0]}, Tls, BootOnLoad)}>
		<PackageConfig title="Perceive-act head" description="The robot's browser head"/>
		<DefaultAppRoutes/>
		<RoutesDir src="examples/perceive_act/head/routes"/>
		<!-- the workspace assets tree at /assets: the wasm binary the pages boot
		     (/assets/wasm/beet.wasm) and the robot-eyes sprites the face renders
		     (/assets/extra/robot-eyes/joy.png). The examples tree at /examples serves
		     the head program the browser fetches. -->
		<AssetsDir src="assets" prefix="assets"/>
		<AssetsDir src="examples" prefix="examples"/>
	</Router>
</Fragment>
